summary:
The Security Council, having considered the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force of 1 June 2006 (S/2006/333) and reaffirming its resolution 1308 (2000) of 17 July 2000, 
1. Calls upon the parties concerned to implement immediately its resolution 338 (1973) of 22 October 1973; 
2. Welcomes the efforts of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force to implement the Secretary-Generalâ€™s zero tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, requests the Secretary-General to continue taking necessary action and keep the Security Council informed, and urges troop-contributing countries to investigate and punish such acts involving their personnel; 
3. Decides to renew the mandate of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force for six months, until 31 December 2006; 
4. Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338 (1973) at the end of this period.
